2 SENATE BILL 496
1 Annotated Code of Maryland
2 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
3 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
4 Article – Health – General
5 Section 15–103(a)(2)(xxvii) and (xxviii)
6 Annotated Code of Maryland
7 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Health – General
10 Section 15–103(a)(2)(xxix) and 15–160
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Health – General
16 15–103.
17 (a) (1) The Secretary shall administer the Maryland Medical Assistance
18 Program.
19 (2) The Program:
20 (xxvii) Beginning on January 1, 2026, if providing coverage for
21 the delivery of anesthesia, shall provide coverage for the delivery of anesthesia in
22 accordance with § 15–862 of the Insurance Article; [and]
23 (xxviii) Beginning on January 1, 2026, shall provide calcium score
24 testing in accordance with § 15–863 of the Insurance Article; AND
25 (XXIX) BEGINNING ON JANUARY 1, 2027, MAY PROVIDE
26 COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE FOR THE TREATMENT OF OBESITY UNDER § 15–160 OF
27 THIS SUBTITLE.
28 15–160.
29 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE FOR THE TREATMENT
30 OF OBESITY” INCLUDES COVERAGE FOR INTENSIVE BEHAVIORAL THERAPY,
31 BARIATRIC SURGERY, AND ANY MEDICATION APPROVED BY THE FEDERAL FOOD
32 AND DRUG ADMINISTRATION WITH AN INDICATION FOR CHRONIC WEIGHT
33 MANAGEMENT IN PATIENTS WITH OBESITY.

SENATE BILL 496 3
1 (B) THE PROGRAM MAY PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE FOR THE
2 TREATMENT OF OBESITY.
3 (C) THE PROGRAM MAY UNDERTAKE UTILIZATION MANAGEMENT TO
4 DETERMINE THE MEDICAL NECESSITY AND APPROPRIATENESS FOR TREATMENT OF
5 OBESITY UNDER THIS SECTION IF THE DETERMINATIONS ARE MADE IN THE SAME
6 MANNER AS DETERMINATIONS ARE MADE FOR THE TREATMENT OF ANY OTHER
7 ILLNESS, CONDITION, OR DISORDER COVERED BY THE PROGRAM.
8 (D) IF THE DEPARTMENT ELECTS TO PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE
9 FOR THE TREATMENT OF OBESITY UNDER THIS SECTION, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL
10 PROVIDE NOTICE TO PROGRAM RECIPIENTS.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Maryland Department of
12 Health may apply to the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services for a State plan
13 amendment that authorizes the State to provide comprehensive coverage for the treatment of
14 obesity.
15 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before November 1,
16 2027, the Maryland Department of Health shall report to the Senate Finance Committee,
17 the Senate Budget and Taxation Committee, the House Health Committee, and the House
18 Appropriations Committee, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article,
19 on whether the Maryland Medical Assistance Program has begun to provide comprehensive
20 coverage for the treatment of obesity as authorized under § 15–160 of the Health – General
21 Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, and if not, why the Department has not begun
22 to provide coverage.
23 SECTION 3. 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
24 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
